    "content": "nullExperience Cloud\nTABLE OF CONTENTS\nClose\nClose\nSearch\nSearch\n Experience Cloud\n Understand the Basics\n Plan & Prepare\n Set Up & Configure\n Manage Users and Data Access\n Build & Customize\n Create Use-Case Driven Sites\n Secure Your Site\n Test & Deploy\n Manage & Moderate\n Managers, Moderators, and Admins Working Together\n Experience Cloud Site Moderation Strategies and Tools\n Organize Experience Cloud Sites with Topics\n Customize Recommendations in Experience Cloud Sites\n Gamification\n Recognition Badges\n Recognition Badges Limitations\n Recognition Badges Setup\n Enable WDC Thanks\n Turn On Recognition Badges in Experience Workspaces\n Configure Who Can Create Recognition Badges\n Configure Who Can Assign Recognition Badges\n Use Components to Display Assigned Recognition Badges on Member...\n Create, Edit, and Delete Recognition Badges\n Manage Who Can Assign a Specific Recognition Badge\n Display the Full List of Assigned Recognition Badges on a Member’s...\n Missions\n Assign Recognition Badges to Experience Cloud Site Members\n Delete Assigned Badges\n Use the API to Give Recognition Badges Sample Code\n Reputation Overview\n Share a Link to Your Experience Cloud Site\n Switch Between Your Salesforce Org and Your Experience Cloud Sites\n Use Reporting in Experience Cloud Sites\n Considerations\n\nYou are here:\n\nSALESFORCE HELP\nDOCS\nEXPERIENCE CLOUD\nConfigure Who Can Create Recognition Badges\n\nUse permission sets, our recommended method, to choose which members can create recognition badges. Restricting who can do so helps control the number of badges in your site and maintains the value of a badge.\n\nREQUIRED EDITIONS AND USER PERMISSIONS\nAvailable in: Enterprise, Professional, Unlimited, and Developer editions.\n\n\nUSER PERMISSIONS NEEDED\nTo create permission sets:\t“Manage Profiles and Permission Sets”\nTo assign permission sets:\t“Assign Permission Sets”\n\nSay that you create a recognition badge to be given to MVPs. Restricting who can create badges helps eliminate the risk of having multiple MVP badges. Restricting who can give the badge to, say, community managers helps make sure only those members who are truly MVPs receive recognition for it.\n\nFirst, set up the permission set for creating badges. From Setup, enter Permission Sets in the Quick Find box, then select Permission Sets.\nClick New.\nEnter your permission set information. Name the permission set “Create Custom Badge Definitions.”\nClick System Permissions and then click Edit.\nTo add the permissions for creating a badge, select Create custom Badge Definitions permission.\nSelect Manage Assignments and add those users you want to let create badges.\nDID THIS ARTICLE SOLVE YOUR ISSUE?\nLet us know so we can improve!\nYes\nNo\n ",
